of effective use of sound, art, and game controls in creating meaningful play. Development of fully functioning and engaging games, following standard domain-specific software development processes and using physical prototyping and playtesting. Current, industrytested game engines.', 'Website (e.g. Moodle), Slides (e.g. Powerpoint), other', 'Salen and Zimmerman , "Rules of Play: Game Design Fundamentals", 2004
The MIT Press, ISBN 0-262-24045-9 
